    <text id="B1150T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell submits information about himself and several other Bureau Agents,
                    including John W. Jordan, the agent in Augusta County.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr><lb/>Headquarters 9<hi rend="super">th</hi> Sub <abbr
                            expan="District">Dist</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bt. Brig
                        Gen.</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr><lb/>Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-08-04"><abbr expan="August">Augt</abbr> 4<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>General</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>In compliance with Circular Letter dated Office C.Q.M. &amp; D.O. <abbr
                        expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">Bu. R.F. &amp;
                        A.L.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr> of <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr> July 29<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1868
                    I have the honor to make the following report viz:</p>

                <p><hi rend="underline">John A. McDonnell</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">Commissioned</hi> Captain 28<hi rend="super">th</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Massachusetts Volunteers">Mass vols</abbr>
                    <hi rend="underline"><abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 8<hi rend="super">th</hi>
                        1861</hi>. Transfered to <abbr expan="Veterans Reserve Corps">V.R.C.</abbr>
                    and commission as Captain in that Corps dated July 27. 1863. <hi
                        rend="underline">Mustered out</hi> of service <hi rend="underline"><abbr
                            expan="January">Jany</abbr> 1. 1868</hi>. Service <hi rend="underline"
                        >continuous</hi> from <abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 8<hi rend="super"
                    >th</hi> 1861 <hi rend="underline">Employed as <abbr
                            expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.A.Comr</abbr></hi>
                    <abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">Bu. R.F.
                        &amp; A.L.</abbr> at the time of muster out.</p>

                <p><hi rend="underline">E.H. Ripley</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">Commissioned</hi> 1<hi rend="super">st</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lieut</abbr> 8<hi rend="super">th</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Connecticut Volunteers">Conn. vols.</abbr> March 2<hi rend="super"
                        >d</hi> 1862. <abbr expan="Commissioned">"</abbr> Captain <abbr
                        expan="8th Connecticut Volunteers">"</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="August">Augt</abbr> 15 1862 <abbr expan="Commissioned Captain">" "</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Veterans Reserve Corps">VRC</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 30<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1863. <hi
                        rend="underline">Mustered out</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">
                        <abbr expan="January">Jany</abbr>
                    </hi> 1 1868 service continuous from <pb n="2"/>March 2<hi rend="super">d</hi>
                    1862, was <hi rend="underline">employed as <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">A.S.A.C.</abbr></hi> in
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr> at date of muster out.</p>

                <p><hi rend="underline">John W. Jordan</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">Commissioned</hi> Major 57<hi rend="super">th</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Indiana">Ind.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Infantry">Infy</abbr>
                    <hi rend="underline"><abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 10/61</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline">Resigned</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline"><abbr expan="November">Nov</abbr> 22<hi rend="super"
                        >nd</hi> 62</hi> - Commissioned 1<hi rend="super">st</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Lieutenant">Lt</abbr> &amp; <abbr expan="Adjutant">adjt</abbr>
                        53<hi rend="super">d</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Kentucky">Ky</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Volunteers">vols</abbr> June 1<hi rend="super">st</hi> 1863.
                    Resigned <abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 1<hi rend="super">st</hi> 1863. <hi
                        rend="underline">Commissioned</hi> Captain <abbr
                        expan="Veterans Reserve Corps">V.R.C.</abbr>
                    <hi rend="underline">June 18, 1864</hi>. <hi rend="underline">Mustered out</hi>
                    <hi rend="underline"><abbr expan="January">Jany</abbr> 1. 1868</hi>. was <hi
                        rend="underline">employed as <abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >S.A.Comr</abbr></hi>
                    <abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">Bu R. F.
                        &amp; A. L.</abbr> at time of muster out. <hi rend="underline">Service
                        not continuous</hi>.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obdt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">St</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
